## Description
<p><img src='data:image/png;base64,'/></p>

<h1>Overview</h1>
<p>The Kartaverse "PT" data nodes allow you to access PTGui Pro v11-12 based .pts (JSON) 360VR stitching project files in Fusion using parametric node-based operators. The letters "PT" stand for Pano Tools. The PT fuse nodes make it easy to parametrically extract values from a .pts file. Changes made in the PTGui project file are automatically reflected in your Fusion node graph.</p>

<h2>Requirements</h2>
<p>The "PT" data nodes depend on the installation of Vonk Ultra from the Reactor Package Manager.</p>

<h2>Example Comps:</h2>

<p>The Kartaverse PT example comps are installed on your system in the "AllData:/Reactor/" PathMap folder path of:<br>
<a href="file://Reactor:/Deploy/Comps/Kartaverse/PT/Demo PT/">Reactor:/Deploy/Comps/Kartaverse/PT/Demo PT/</a></p>

<p>The Reactor Package Manager has an extra downloadable example project named:<br>
"Kartaverse/KartaVP/Comps/KartaVP Example | Caguas VP"</p>

<h2>For More Info:</h2>
<h3>Kartaverse PT Docs</h3>
<p><a href="https://github.com/Kartaverse/PT-Data-Nodes-Docs">https://github.com/Kartaverse/PT-Data-Nodes-Docs</a></p>
